record.name: ADH101 AIR TRACK
record.help: This message contains data associated with an air track received from the tactical data link. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon initial receipt or subsequent receipts of a remote air track passing the receipt filters. Upon initial receipt and until host System Track Number attribution, the "SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER" field is set to value 0. Upon receipt of: - An air unit message, the "TRACK_TYPE" field is set to value (PPLI). - An indirect air unit message, the "TRACK_TYPE" field is set to value (INDIRECT_PPLI). - A track message the "TRACK_TYPE" field is set to value (TRACK). In case of difference between a system data (with local component) and remote (Env/Cat, Identity, IFF/SIF): - the "CONFLICT_INDICATOR" field is set to a significant value in order to identify the difference detected, - and the "CONFLICT_REASON_AMPLIFICATION" field informs about the origin of the Identity difference detected. - If the difference concerns IFF data, the "MODE_I/II/III/IV_CODE_APPLICABILITY" is set in accordance with the IFF data difference detected. At the first detected difference, the DLIP stops going on its difference processing. The order of difference detection on a track is Env/Cat, Identity and IFF/SIF.

record.name: ADH106 EW PRODUCT
record.help: This message contains data associated with EW product data received from the tactical data link. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of a remote EW product passing the receipt filters. Upon initial receipt and until host System Track Number attribution, the "SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER" field is set to value 0. In case of the difference between a system data (with local component) and remote data is assumed by the DLIP: - the "CONFLICT_INDICATOR" field is set to a significant value in order to identify the difference detected (environment/category and identity), - and the "CONFLICT_REASON_AMPLIFICATION" field informs about the origin of the Identity difference detected. At the first detected difference, the DLIP stops going on its difference processing. The order of difference detection on a track is Env/Cat and Identity.

When the "SLAVED_INDICATOR" field is set in the message, the LATITUDE and LONGITUDE fields contain respectively a delta latitude and a delta longitude value from the related track position (TRACK_IDENTIFIER_RELATED).

record.name: ADH108 EMERGENCY POINT

record.name: ADH121 DROP TRACK
record.help: This message contains data to notify to the host that a remote entity (track, point, EW product, area, line) will never be received. This message is transmitted by the DLIP in the following cases : - Receipt of a remote drop track message, - When the DLIP takes R on a track previously received on the data link, - After staleness limit of a non received track, - When a remote track becomes filtered, - When the related track of the concerned slaved object is dropped, to drop the remote component of the track.

record.name: ADH122 IDENTITY DIFFERENCE REPORT
record.help: This message contains data extracted from tactical data link messages to notify the host, an identity difference. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of : - a difference report message, - a change data order message, when received identity is different from the system track identity. Moreover, the DLIP fulfils the "CONFLICT_REASON_AMPLIFICATION" field with the origin of the difference.

record.name: ADH123 CATEGORY DIFFERENCE ALERT
record.help: This message contains data extracted from tactical data link messages to notify the host that an environment/category conflict has been detected by the DLIP. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of a difference report message when received environment/category is in conflict with the system track environment/category.

record.name: ADH124 TRACK IDENTIFIER
record.help: This message contains data to indicate all the link track numbers of the given system track. This message is transmitted by the DLIP to the host upon receipt of a track identifier report message.

record.name: ADH126 EMERGENCY STATUS UPDATE
record.help: This message contains the emergency status of a given track received from the tactical data link. This message can be considered as the event for the change of the emergency status. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of : - an emergency status change message, - a PPLI message when emergency indicator changes whatever the value of this indicator, - a track message when emergency indicator changes to emergency status.

record.name: ADH127 FORCE TELL STATUS UPDATE
record.help: This message contains the force tell status of a given track received from the tactical data link. This message can be considered as the event for the change of the force tell status. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of : - a force tell status change message, - a PPLI message when force tell indicator changes whatever the value of this indicator, - a track message when force tell indicator changes to force tell status.

record.name: ADH128 STRENGTH UPDATE
record.help: This message contains new strength value of a given track received from the tactical data link. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of a strength change message when the DLIP decide to automatically accept the remote data (if own unit is not controlling unit).

record.name: ADH129 STRENGTH DIFFERENCE ALERT
record.help: This message contains the received strength value and the system strength value of a given track. When the DLIP detects a strength difference and that own unit is controlling unit of the concerned track, this message is transmitted to the C host system upon receipt of : - a strength change message, - a track message when received strength value differs from system strength value.

record.name: ADH130 EXERCISE STATUS ORDER
record.help: This message is used to change the identity of all the exercise tracks to "Friend". This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of an exercise status order message.

record.name: ADH131 TRACK IDENTIFIER REQUEST
record.help: This message contains a track identifier request received from the data link. This message is sent, by the DLIP, to forward to the host a track identifier request received from the data link.

record.name: ADH132 DATA REQUEST
record.help: This message request intelligence, EW control/coordination and/or filter data. This message is sent by the DLIP to the host upon receipt of a data update request message which requires the transmission of intelligence, EW control/coordination and/or filter data. This request may be by indicator or by track number. In case of request by indicator, the host shall transmit to the DLIP all intelligence data when intelligence data request indicator is set, all EW control/coordination data when EW request indicator is set, filter data when filter request indicator is set and in accordance with filter identifier requested. In case of request by track number the host shall transmit to the DLIP intelligence and/or EW control/coordination data related to the given track.

record.name: ADH133 POINTER
record.help: This message contains data to designate a geographic position on one or more host displays. This geographic position is defined in the following messages received from the data link. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of a pointer message. All the data in the TARGET_POINTER_DATA record are available only if the TARGET_POINTER_DATA_INDICATOR field is set.

record.name: ADH135 TRACK IDENTIFIER UPDATE
record.help: This message contains data to indicate an assignment of a link track number to a track with only local component. This message is transmitted for each link ID by the DLIP when the DLIP allocates a Link Track Number : - to a new system track eligible for transmission, - to an existing track when the DLIP answers to a change link Track Number received from the host. It is also transmitted by DLIP in response to an AHD337 request from host to removing a system track and LTN associations. In this case, one AHD135 will always be sent per link id with the LINK_TRACK_NUMBER set to 0.

record.name: ADH137 ASSOCIATION
record.help: This message is used to create or terminate a remote track association. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of a creation or end of a remote track association message.

record.name: ADH138 CLEAR IFF
record.help: This message is used to clear some IFF Mode Values. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of a clear IFF message.

record.name: ADH139 IFF DIFFERENCE ALERT
record.help: This message contains data to notify the host an IFF difference, This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of an IFF difference report message when received data are in conflict with the system ones (with local component).

record.name: ADH141 IFF SPECIAL CODE UPDATE
record.help: This message contains the new IFF Special Code Values and Mode Indicators. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of an IFF special code report.

record.name: ADH142 WEAPON ENGAGEMENT STATUS
record.help: This message contains data extracted from data link messages and associated to an engagement status of a friendly weapon system track and a target. This message reports only one engagement status. This message is transmitted by the DLIP to the host system upon reception of a creation, update or end of an engagement status message. This message is transmitted by the DLIP in the following cases : - Upon receipt of a first engagement status message concerning a unit, - Upon modification of an engagement status, - Upon receipt of a "terminate engagement" message, - After drop of a C system track holding engagements, - After drop of a system track being the subject of an engagement, - Staleness of weapon engagement status.

record.name: ADH143 TAKING CONTROL REQUEST
record.help: For such a message, the own unit is the loser platform. This message contains data concerning a request to transfer the control of a non C JU. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of a handover message where the originator requests the control transfer of a given non C JU. The "HANDOVER_DATA" record contains technical control data used by the non C JU in handover process.

record.name: ADH144 THREAT WARNING
record.help: This message provides received remote threat warning data. This message is transmitted by the DLIP to the host upon receipt of a data link threat warning message.

record.name: ADH145 CONTROLING UNIT REPORT
record.help: This message contains data extracted from data links messages identifying the C controlling unit of a friendly unit. This message is transmitted by the DLIP : - Upon receipt of a WILCO response associated to a mission assignment sent to a non-controlled unit or a controlling unit change. - Upon receipt of a first remote controlling unit report message, - Upon modification of controlling unit status, - Upon receipt a "terminate controlling unit report " message, - After drop of a C system track holding controlling unit report, - After drop of a system track being the subject of an controlling unit report, - Staleness of controlling unit data.

record.name: ADH146 PAIRING
record.help:
This message contains data extracted from data link messages to create, update or terminate a pairing. This message is transmitted by the DLIP in the following cases : - Upon receipt of a WILCO response associated to a mission assignment or a controlling unit change. - Upon receipt of a first remote pairing message, - Upon modification of a remote pairing, - Upon receipt of a "terminate pairing" message, - After drop of a C system track holding pairing, - After drop of a system track being the subject of a pairing, - Staleness of pairing data.
The "LINK_IDENTIFICATION" field is set to "NO_STATEMENT" value when the message concerns a pairing on which own platform has the transmit responsibility.

record.name: ADH147 COMMAND ORDER
record.help: This message contains command data addressed to the host and received on the tactical data link. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of a command message.

record.name: ADH148 INTELLIGENCE DATA
record.help: This message contains remote intelligence data. This message is transmitted by the DLIP to the host upon receipt of an intelligence data message from the link.

record.name: ADH150 ECCM COORDINATION
record.help: This message provides the means to coordinate and direct Electronic Counter-Counter measures activities with an other C unit. This message is transmitted by the DLIP to the host upon receipt of an ECCM coordination message from the data link.

record.name: ADH152 CONTROL UNIT CHANGE ORDER
record.help: This message contains data extracted from a control request message received from a non-C JU. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of a control request.

record.name: ADH155 CANCEL HANDOVER
record.help: This message contains necessary data to send a cancel handover message. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon reception of a cancellation handover message from the remote unit with which the handover is processed.

record.name: ADH156 GIVING CONTROL REQUEST
record.help: For such a message, the own unit is the winner platform. This message contains data to request the local platform to take the control of a given non-C JU. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of a handover message where the originator requests to give the control of a given non-C JU.

record.name: ADH157 GIVING CONTROL RESPONSE
record.help: For such a message, the own unit is the loser platform. This message contains response data associated to a current handover procedure initiated by the local platform. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon receipt of a handover response. The "HANDOVER_DATA" record contains technical control data used by the non-C JU in handover process. Because of additional data in the response, this message is an exception to the normal R/C processing and replace the ADH190_RC_RESPONSE message.

record.name: ADH167 VOICE CALLSIGN DATA
record.help: This message provides the voice call sign received on link 11 for an aircraft or a special point. This message is transmitted by the DLIP to the host upon receipt of a link 11 voice call sign message (M9E1) except in case of reception following a handover message (M10A). In this last case, the voice call sign data will be provided to the host in the appropriate handover message.

The "HOST_SEQUENCE_NUMBER" field contains a value allowing the local platform to identify which addressed message is associated with the response received. The "RECEIPT_COMPLIANCE" field indicates the expected response for a message using the R/C protocol.
