record.name: ADH320 DUPLICATE TN ALERT
record.help: This message contains data to notify to the host that a duplicate Track Number conflict has been detected by the DLIP. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon detection of duplicate TN conflict. Several cases are possible : - Receipt of a remote track with a link TN which points out a system point, - Receipt of a remote point with a link TN which points out a system track, - Receipt of a remote track or point for which a geographical inconsistency has been detected. In this message, TRACK_NUMBER_ORIGINATOR identifies the IU originator of the track in conflict and TRACK_IDENTIFIER_KNOWN indicates the track number in conflict and the system track number of the currently known track. The Longitude, Latitude and Altitude data of this message are those of the received track in conflict with the DLIP system track or point. The received track in Track Number conflict is not transmitted to the host. Upon such a conflict, the received track or point message is discarded.

record.name: ADH325 TRACK STATUS
record.help: This message can contain the transmission status of a given track and, if the track is filtered, the filter type which has blocked the transmission or the staleness status of a received track. This message is transmitted by the DLIP to the host when the transmission status of a given track change (TRANSMISSION_STATUS) or when the DLIP staleness processing begins on a received track (STALENESS_STATUS). The staleness mechanism is switched on after [TQ_Start_Decrement] seconds elapsed and the track quality is decremented one by one each [TQ_Start_Decrement] seconds. [TQ_Start_Decrement] is set in the MP.Param DLIP configuration file.

record.name: ADH334 DL CORRELATION REQUEST
record.help: This message is used by DLIP to notify to the host a correlation request received from a data-link. This message is transmitted by the DLIP to the C host system upon reception of a correlation message, if it recognises a correlation request originated by a remote unit. The DLIP forwards to the host : - The identification of the link from which the request has been received, - The addressee of the requests originator, - The system track number associated with the link track to be retained, - The link track number of the track to be retained, - The system track number associated with the link track to be dropped, - The link track number of the track to be dropped, - The Response Value (RV) requested : -- If the request is received from link 16 : RV could be set to value 0 (reverse correlation is acceptable) or to value 1 (reverse correlation is not acceptable) -- If the request is received from link 11 : RV is always set with value 1. When the field SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER of the retained object is not filled (no statement value), the C2 shall interpret this message as a correlation message but also as a TN change message. The unique identification of the request that must be used by the host in its response is contained in the sequence number of the header.

record.name: ADH336 DL CORRELATION RESPONSE
record.help: This message is used by DLIP to notify to the host a correlation response received from a data-link to a previously initiated request. This message is transmitted by the DLIP to the C host system upon reception of a correlation message which matches a correlation request previously initiated by the host. This response may be a reversion or a rejection of the correlation requested by the host and may be received only on link 16. The DLIP forwards to the host : - The identification of the link from which the response has been received, - The addressee of the responses originator, - The system track number of the track to be retained, - The link track number of the track to be retained, - The system track number of the track to be dropped, - The link track number of the track to be dropped, - The Response Value (RV) given by the remote unit : -- RV could be set to value 1 if the remote unit requests a reverse correlation or to value 2 if the remote unit rejects the correlation. - The unique identification of the previously initiated request. If the RV field is set to 1, this correlation shall be considered as a superseded one and the new unique identification of the correlation is contained in the SEQUENCE_NUMBER field.

record.name: ADH418 AWCIES TARGET
record.help:
This message contains all information received from the L16 network in a target report message (J12.6) that must be routed to an adjacent remote RPC through AWCIES.
Data organization : The organization of a ADH418_AWCIES_TARGET is quite the same as a ADH118_TARGET message. Upon receipt of a target report (J12.6) from L16, the DLIP determines the routing filter for which the target is located in and when found, build this message to route target data to the corresponding remote RPC site through AWCIES. The DLIP sets in the message the sites addressees. Field ACC_SITE_ADDRESSEE identifies the local ACC site which originates this message. Field RPC_SITE_ADDRESSEE identifies the remote RPC site which will be responsible to correlate the target. The DLIP sets in the record TRACK_IDENTIFIER_ORIGINATOR the identifier of the non C2 which originated the target report and in the field INDEX_NUMBER the index of the target as received in J12.6 message.
The Permanent_Bloc is described in the table below :

record.name: ADH419 AWCIES TARGET CORRELATION
record.help: This message contains the host system track number assignment to a routed target. It is used by an RPC to pass to a remote ACC a track/target correlation/de-correlation message through AWCIES. The DLIP sets in the message the sites addressees. Field RPC_SITE_ADDRESSEE identifies the local RPC site which originates this message.Field ACC_SITE_ADDRESSEE identifies the remote ACC site which will be responsible to process the message.

record.name: AHD101 SYSTEM AIR TRACK
record.help: This message is received by the DLIP upon creation of a system air track and updates of data. The "LOCAL_TRACK_COMPONENT_INDICATOR" field shall be set if the system air track has a local component. This field is used by the DLIP to perform R assumption and conflict detection. As the R management is assumed by the DLIP, the "TRACK QUALITY" field shall be filled by the host only with the local value of the track quality. The system air track shall be sent on initiation of the system track and on change of any data.

field.name: PPLI TRACK NUMBER AND IDENTITY INDICATOR

record.name: AHD102 SYSTEM SURFACE TRACK
record.help: This message is received by the DLIP upon creation of a system surface track and updates of data more than GEOGRAPHIC_INFORMATION. The "LOCAL_TRACK_COMPONENT_INDICATOR" field shall be set if the system surface track has a local component. This field is used by the DLIP to perform R assumption and conflict detection. As the R management is assumed by the DLIP, the "TRACK QUALITY" field shall be filled by the host only with the local value of the track quality. The system surface track shall be sent on initiation of the system track and on change of data.

field.name: PPLI TRACK NUMBER AND IDENTITY INDICATOR

record.name: AHD103 SYSTEM SUBSURFACE TRACK
record.help: This message is received by the DLIP upon creation of a system subsurface track and updates of data. The "LOCAL_TRACK_COMPONENT_INDICATOR" field shall be set if the system subsurface track has a local component. This field is used by the DLIP to perform R2 assumption.

field.name: PPLI TRACK NUMBER AND IDENTITY INDICATOR

record.name: AHD104 SYSTEM LAND POINT
record.help: This message is received by the DLIP upon creation of a system land point and updates of data. No specific recommendation is expected for this message.

field.name: PPLI TRACK NUMBER AND IDENTITY INDICATOR
TIME TAG UTM TIME OF VALIDITY

record.name: AHD105 SYSTEM LAND TRACK
record.help: This message is received by the DLIP upon creation of a system land track and updates of data. As the R management is assumed by the DLIP, the "TRACK QUALITY" field shall be filled by the host only with the local value of the track quality. The "LOCAL_TRACK_COMPONENT_INDICATOR" field shall be set if the system land track has a local component. This field is used by the DLIP to perform R assumption and conflict detection. The system land track (AHD105_SYSTEM_LAND_TRACK) shall be sent on initiation of the system track.

field.name: PPLI TRACK NUMBER AND IDENTITY INDICATOR
TIME TAG UTM TIME OF VALIDITY

record.name: AHD106 SYSTEM EW PRODUCT
record.help: This message is received by the DLIP upon creation of a system EW product track and updates of data. As the R management is assumed by the DLIP, the "TRACK QUALITY" field shall be filled by the host only with the local value of the track quality. The "LOCAL_TRACK_COMPONENT_INDICATOR" field shall be set if the system EW product has a local component. This field is used by the DLIP to perform R assumption and conflict detection. The system EW product (AHD106_SYSTEM_EW_PRODUCT) shall be sent on initiation of the system track. The maximum update rate shall not be greater than 0.2 Hz.

record.name: AHD107 SYSTEM REFERENCE POINT
record.help: This message is received by the DLIP upon creation of a system reference point and updates of data. If the "LATITUDE" and "LONGITUDE" fields contain respectively delta latitude and delta longitude values of the reference point from the related track position, the "SLAVED_INDICATOR" shall be set.

record.name: AHD108 SYSTEM EMERGENCY POINT
record.help: This message is received by the DLIP upon creation of a system emergency point and updates of data. When any TRACK_NUMBER_PREVIOUSLY_REPORTED is different from NO STATEMENT, SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER_PREVIOUSLY_REPORTED is ignored. . When all TRACK_NUMBER_PREVIOUSLY_REPORTED (if any) are set to NO STATEMENT, they are ignored and SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER_PREVIOUSLY_REPORTED is used in that case.

record.name: AHD110 SYSTEM TN ASSIGN
record.help: This message is received by the DLIP upon creation of a new remote track as a system track. - This message shall be always received before an AHD101_SYSTEM_AIR_TRACK, AHD102_SYSTEM_SURFACE_TRACK, AHD104_SYSTEM_LAND_POINT, AHD105_SYSTEM_LAND_TRACK message, AHD106_SYSTEM_EW_PRODUCT, AHD107_SYSTEM_REFERENCE_POINT, AHD108_SYSTEM_EMERGENCY_POINT, AHD117_SYSTEM_REFERENCE_LINE_AREA. - The SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER field shall always be fulfilled with a new System Track Number.

record.name: AHD116 LOCAL PLATFORM PPLI
record.help: This message contains all local data used to generate the local land PPLI message on the data link. This message is transmitted by the host to the DLIP to set or update local platform PPLI data, in order to send a PPLI message on the data link. This message has only be used when simple resource is used.

field.name: ACTIVE RELAY INDICATOR WIDE AREA NETWORK

record.name: LAND PT PPLI AMP MISSION DATA

field.name: TIME TAG UTM TIME OF VALIDITY

record.name: AHD117 SYSTEM REFERENCE LINE AREA
record.help: This message is received by the DLIP upon creation or updates of data of a system reference line area. No specific recommendation is expected for this message.

record.name: AHD119 TARGET CORRELATION
record.help: This message contains the host system track number assignment to a target. This message shall be sent upon first reception of new target data. The SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER field contains either a new system track number, in case of the creation of a new system track with the received remote target, or an existing system track number in case of the host has correlated the received target with an existing system track.

record.name: AHD121 DROP SYSTEM TRACK
record.help: This message contains the system track number of a dropped system track. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon system track drop. This message is used during correlation processing in full control mode. In this case, it is necessary for the DLIP to: a) if SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER different from NO_STATEMENT value and LINK_IDENTIFICATION=NO_STATEMENT and LINK_TRACK_NUMBER=NO_STATEMENT, - drop the system track, - send drop message on all links where it has R. b) if SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER=NO_STATEMENT and LINK_IDENTIFICATION different from NO_STATEMENT value and LINK_TRACK_NUMBER different from NO_STATEMENT value, - send a drop message on the specified link. c) if SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER, LINK_IDENTIFICATION and LINK_TRACK_NUMBER different from NO_STATEMENT value, - drop the system track, - send a drop message on the specified link. If the C wants to send the drop message on more than one link, an AHD121 is necessary for each link.

record.name: AHD122 IDENTITY DIFFERENCE REPORT
record.help: This message contains the host decision related to an identity difference detected by the DLIP. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon operator response or host automatic resolution to an identity conflict. This decision concerns the system track identity and if there is a pending conflict on each link, this message is the response for all the conflicts.

record.name: AHD123 CATEGORY DIFFERENCE RESOLUTION
record.help: This message contains the host decision related to an environment/category difference detected by the DLIP. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon operator decision concerning an environment/category conflict detected previously by the DLIP. This decision concerns the system track env/cat and if there is a pending conflict on each link, this message is the response for all the conflicts.

record.name: AHD125 CHANGE DATA ORDER
record.help: This message contains data necessary to send a change data order message on data links. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon operator action to send a change data order message. The change data order is sent on all the data links on which the track is known.

record.name: AHD126 DATA UPDATE REQUEST
record.help: This message contains necessary data to send a data update request message on data links.This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon operator action to request data about a track or point on data links. To broadcast this message : - The "COLLECTIVE_ADDRESS_INDICATOR" field shall be set, - And all the fields of the LIST_OF_ADDRESSEES record shall be filled with the default value. The data update request is sent on all the links (if this is a request by track number, the TN shall be known on the link). To address this message up to five given units : - The "COLLECTIVE_ADDRESS_INDICATOR" field shall not be set, - And the LIST_OF_ADDRESSEES record shall contain the addressees, in a numerical order and all the fields not used shall be filled with the default value.

field.name: MISSILE WEAPON SYSTEM STATUS DATA REQUEST INDICATOR
ELECTRONIC WARFARE FIXES DATA REQUEST INDICATOR

record.name: AHD128 TRACK IDENTIFIER
record.help: This message contains data to report all the link track numbers of the given system track. This message is transmitted by the C host system to the DLIP when it wants to transmit all the known link track numbers on the link.

record.name: AHD129 TRACK IDENTIFIER REQUEST
record.help: This message contains the link track number applicabilities for which the host requests information. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon operator action to request the track number allocated for a given track or point on one or several given data links (specified by the different data links applicability fields).

record.name: AHD130 EXERCISE STATUS ORDER
record.help: This message allows to DLIP to transmit an exercise status order message. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon operator action to send an exercise status order message.

record.name: AHD132 POINTER
record.help:
This message contains data to designate a geographic position to one or more addressed units. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon operator action to send a pointer message on data link. - The "LATITUDE" and "LONGITUDE" fields are mandatory. - The "SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER_SUBJECT" should be filled with a system track number to send a pointer to a non C unit. But if this field is non significant, it should be filled with '0'.
- To broadcast this message only towards C units : -- The "COLLECTIVE_ADDRESS_INDICATOR" field shall be set, -- And all the fields of the LIST_OF_ADDRESSEES record shall be filled with the default value. - To address this message up to five given units : -- The "COLLECTIVE_ADDRESS_INDICATOR" field shall not be set, -- And the LIST_OF_ADDRESSEES record shall contain the addressees, in a numerical order and all the fields not used shall be filled with the default value.

record.name: AHD137 ASSOCIATION
record.help: This message contains data to create or terminate a host track association. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon operator action to create or to end a local track association

record.name: AHD138 CLEAR IFF
record.help: This message is used to clear some IFF Mode Values. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon operator action to transmit a clear IFF message on a given data link. If the operator wants to send a clear IFF message on all data links, he can do this by putting NO_STATEMENT value in the LINK_IDENTIFICATION field. Upon receipt of this message, the DLIP clear the requested IFF of the system track.

record.name: AHD139 IFF DIFFERENCE REPORT
record.help: This message contains the host operator decision concerning an IFF conflict detected by the DLIP. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon operator response to an IFF conflict (ADH139_IFF_DIFFERENCE_ALERT).

record.name: AHD140 IFF UPDATE REQUEST
record.help: This message contains the IFF mode indicators for which the host requests an IFF update. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon operator action to transmit an IFF data update request message on a given data link.

record.name: AHD141 IFF SPECIAL CODE UPDATE
record.help: This message contains the new IFF Special Code Values and Indicators. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon operator action to allocate or modify IFF special codes of a given track on a given data link.

record.name: AHD142 WEAPON ENGAGEMENT STATUS
record.help: This message contains necessary data to send a weapon engagement status message of a friendly weapon system and a target. This message is received by the DLIP upon creation, update or removal of an engagement status.

record.name: AHD143 TAKING CONTROL REQUEST
record.help: This message contains necessary data to send an handover taking control request. For such a message, the own unit is the winner platform. This message is transmitted by the C host system to the DLIP when an host operator decide to request taking control of an aircraft to an other C unit. The record UNIT_IDENTIFIER_ADDRESSEE contains data to address the host message to a given unit on the data link. The "HANDOVER_DATA" record contains technical control data used by the nonCJU in handover process. It is the host reponsability to check that the non-C unit object of the handover is under the control of the addressed C unit.

record.name: AHD144 THREAT WARNING
record.help: This message provides threat warning data on a given unit. This message is transmitted by the host to the DLIP when the host recognize an immediate threat to another unit. In case of COLLECTIVE_ADDRESS_INDICATOR field set, this message will be broadcasted with collective address value, the fields SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER and LINK_IDENTIFICATION will not be used by the DLIP.

record.name: AHD145 CONTROLLING UNIT REPORT
record.help: This message contains data to indicate that the local platform is controlling a given unit. This message is received by the DLIP upon : - initialisation of the control on a given nonC unit, - controlling unit data updates, - removal order of DLIP stored controlling unit data (after staleness).

record.name: AHD146 PAIRING
record.help: This message contains necessary data to send a pairing message to create or terminate a local pairing. This message is received by the DLIP upon : - creation of a local pairing, - "terminate" of a pairing under own platform trasmission responsidility, - removal order of DLIP stored pairing (after staleness).

record.name: AHD147 COMMAND ORDER
record.help: This message contains necessary data to send a command order message on tactical data links. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon operator action to send a command order. The record UNIT_IDENTIFIER_ADDRESSEE contains data to address this message to a given unit or to broadcast it on the data link. In case of COLLECTIVE_ADDRESS_INDICATOR field set, this message will be broadcasted with collective address value, the fields SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER and LINK_IDENTIFICATION will not be used by the DLIP.

record.name: AHD148 INTELLIGENCE DATA
record.help: This message provides local intelligence data. This message is transmitted by the host to the DLIP when the host decides to transmit intelligence data on the data link.

record.name: AHD150 ECCM COORDINATION
record.help: This message provides the means to coordinate and direct Electronic Counter-Countermeasures activities with an other C unit. This message is transmitted by the host to the DLIP when the host decides to transmit Electronic Counter-Countermeasures coordination data on the data link. The record UNIT_IDENTIFIER_ADDRESSEE contains data to address this message to a given unit on the data link. This message must be transmitted with R/C value set to 0 and will never be send with collective address.

record.name: AHD151 VECTOR ORDER
record.help: This message contains necessary data to send a vector message. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon operator action to send a vector. The record UNIT_IDENTIFIER_ADDRESSEE contains data to address this message to a given unit or to broadcast it on the data link. In case of COLLECTIVE_ADDRESS_INDICATOR field set, this message will be broadcasted with collective address value, the fields SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER and LINK_IDENTIFICATION will not be used by the DLIP.

record.name: AHD152 CONTROL UNIT CHANGE ORDER
record.help: This message is used to initiate the control of the source unit by the local platform or to hand-off the control to an other C unit. This message contains necessary data to send a controlling unit change message in order to : - initiate a change of controlling unit procedure, - end a control procedure. This message is received by the DLIP upon operator decision to : - to take the control of a non-C JU, - to end the control on a non-C JU. The record UNIT_IDENTIFIER_ADDRESSEE contains data to address the controlling unit change message to a given unit on the data link.

field.name: SYSTEM TRACK NUMBER NEW CONTROL AGENCY

record.name: AHD154 FLIGHT PATH
record.help:
This message contains all information about a flight path, a restricted area or an update of a flight path (or restricted area).
Data organisation :
AHD154_FLIGHT_PATH = Permanent_Bloc + List_Of_Arguments.
- Permanent_Bloc = Record HEADER + Permanent_Data. - List_Of_Arguments = One OR more Arguments. -- Argument = Argument_Amp_Point OR Argument_Amp_Zone OR Argument_Point_Desc. --- Argument_Amp_Point = Header_Of_Arg + Record AMPLIFIED_POINT_DESCRIPTION. --- Argument_Amp_Zone = Header_Of_Arg + Record ZONE_AMPLIFICATION_DESCRIPTION. --- Argument_Point_Desc = Header_Of_Arg + Record POINT_DESCRIPTION. This message is transmitted by the C host system to the DLIP when the host decide to transmit a flight path, a restricted area or an update to a given non C unit.
List_Of_Arguments for a creation of a zone : - Argument_Amp_Zone + Three or more (max 15) Argument_Point_Desc.
List_Of_Arguments for a creation of a flight path : - Two or more (max. 15) Argument_Amp_Point.
List_Of_Arguments for an update a flight path : - one Argument_Amp_Point.
List_Of_Arguments for an update a zone : - one Argument_Point_Desc.
The Permanent_Bloc is described in the table below :

record.name: AHD157 GIVING CONTROL REQUEST
record.help: This message contains necessary data to send an handover message with the intention of giving the control of a non C JU to an other C JU. For such a message, the own unit is the loser platform. This message is received by the DLIP upon operator decision to give the control of a non-C JU to an other C JU. The record UNIT_IDENTIFIER_ADDRESSEE contains data to address the handover message to a given C JU on the data link.

record.name: AHD158 GIVING CONTROL RESPONSE
record.help: This message contains the response of the local platform to a remote giving control request. For such a message, the own unit is the winner platform. This message is transmitted by the C host system to the DLIP to answer to a remote giving control request previously sent by the DLIP to the host (ADH156_GIVING_CONTROL_REQUEST). The "HANDOVER_DATA" record contains technical control data used by the non-C JU in handover process. Because of additional data in the response, this message is an exception to the normal R/C processing and replace the AHD190_RC_RESPONSE message.

record.name: AHD159 SET DLTRACK TRANSMISSION MODE
record.help: This message contains the data link identifier and the system track number concerned by this order. This message is transmitted by the C host system to the DLIP upon operator action on the control of the transmission of a track.

record.name: AHD161 CANCEL HANDOVER
record.help: This message contains necessary data to send a cancel handover message. This message is received by the DLIP when an host operator decide to cancel an handover. The record UNIT_IDENTIFIER_ADDRESSEE contains data to address this message to a given unit on the data link.

record.name: AHD162 INFORMATION REQUEST
record.help: This message is used by the host to request redundant reporting of messages ADH135 followed by ADH325. The DLIP processes the request asynchronously and reports to the host the requested messages built with information held in database at the moment of processing. To request redundant reporting of ADH135 and ADH325 messages, the host must fill: - The field SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER with a valid system track number. If the system track number is unknown, DLIP will not report requested messages. - The field LINK_IDENTIFICATION with either NO_STATEMENT value (in this case, the DLIP will report requested messages relative to the specified SysTN for all the known links) either a valid link identification (in this case, the DLIP will report requested messages only for the Link_Id specified).

record.name: AHD163 TARGET TRANSMISSION ORDER
record.help: This message contains the order to allow or stop the transmission of a designated track as target on the control NPG. This message is transmitted by the host to the DLIP when the host decides to begin or to stop the transmission of a target for a current mission.

record.name: AHD167 VOICE CALLSIGN DATA
record.help: This message is used to transmit the voice call sign data concerning a controlled unit or a special point. This message is transmitted by the host to the DLIP when the host allocates the voice call sign to a given unit under local platform control or to a special point. This message may be rejected by the DLIP if the given unit is not under local control or if system track number is unknown from DLIP.

record.name: AHD190 RC RESPONSE
record.help: This message contains data to send the receipt compliance response messages of the local platform associated to the previous message addressed to the local platform and requiring its response. This message is received by the DLIP upon receipt of the local platform response to the previous addressed message requiring its response. The "RECEIPT_COMPLIANCE " shall be fulfilled with the value corresponding to the local platform response. The "DLIP_SEQUENCE_NUMBER" field shall be fulfilled with the same value of the "SEQUENCE_NUMBER" field in the "DATA_HEADER" of the ADHxxx message to which this response corresponds.

record.name: AHD192 MISSION CORRELATOR CHANGE
record.help: This message enables a host acting as controlling unit to add, delete or change mission correlators on a controlled non C2 unit. The DLIP will reject the Mission Correlator Change messages received from the host for a non-C2 unit not under the control of the platform and inform the host about this (with an ADH180).

record.name: AHD200 FREE TEXT
record.help: This message contains all characters of a free text message. This message is transmitted by the C host system to the DLIP when the host decide to transmit a free text to a given addressed unit. The record UNIT_IDENTIFIER_ADDRESSEE contains data to address the host message to a given unit or to broadcast it on the data link. In case of COLLECTIVE_ADDRESS_INDICATOR field set, this message will be broadcasted with collective address value, the fields SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER and LINK_IDENTIFICATION will not be used by the DLIP and shall be filled with the default value. The C host system has to decide which form it wants to transmit setting the field NUMBER_OF_EXTENTION_WORDS.

record.name: AHD210 AIRFIELD STATUS
record.help: This message contains status data of an airfield status message. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon creation or update of airfield status.

field.name: FIRE STREAK AIR TO AIR MISSILE
MAGIC I AIR TO AIR MISSILE
MAGIC II AIR TO AIR MISSILE

record.name: AHD211 AIR PLATFORM STATUS
record.help: This message contains status data of an air platform status message. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon creation or update of air platform status data.

field.name: AIR TO AIR WEAPON RELEASE SYSTEM STATUS
AIR TO GROUND WEAPON RELEASE SYSTEM STATUS

record.name: AHD213 LAND PLATFORM STATUS
record.help: This message contains status data of a land platform status message. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon creation or update of land platform status data.

record.name: AHD219 TARGET DECORRELATION
record.help: This message contains data to indicate the decorrelation from a system track of the target component identified with LINK_IDENTIFICATION field. This message is transmitted by the C host system to the DLIP upon host decision to decorrelate a target component from a system track.

record.name: AHD300 FREE TEXT
record.help: This message contains all characters of a free text message. This message is transmitted by the host system to the DLIP when the host decide to transmit a free text to a given addressed unit. The record UNIT_IDENTIFIER_ADDRESSEE_LINK contains data to address the host message to a given unit or to broadcast it on the data link. In case of COLLECTIVE_ADDRESS_INDICATOR field set, this message will be braodcasted with collective address value, the fields LINK_TRACK_NUMBER_ADDRESSEE and LINK_IDENTIFICATION will not be used by the DLIP and shall be filled with the default value. The C host system has to decide which form it wants to transmit setting the field NUMBER_OF_EXTENTION_WORDS.

record.name: AHD334 CORRELATION REQUEST
record.help:
This message is used by the host to initiate a correlation request on the data-link. Data organization : AHD334_CORRELATION_REQUEST = Permanent_Block + List_Of_Arguments
Permanent_Block = Record HEADER + Permanent_Data. List_Of_Arguments = One OR more Arguments. Argument = Argument_Link_Track_Number_Choice. Argument_Link_Track_Number_Choice = Header_Of_Block + Record LINK_TRACK_NUMBER_CHOICE This message is transmitted by the C host system to the DLIP in two cases : - Upon host decision to correlate two system tracks or to decorrelate an existing remote track and re-correlate it to another existing system track. In this case, CORRELATION_ACTION field shall be set with MULTILINK_TRACK_CORRELATION value or - Upon host decision to correlate a new remote track with an existing system track. In this case, CORRELATION_ACTION field shall be set with NEW_REMOTE_TRACK_CORRELATION value.
In the first case (system track correlation), the record MULTILINK_TRACK_CORRELATION shall be used. The field SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER_RETAINED defines the system track number which will be used for the resulting track. The field SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER_DROPPED defines the system track number to be dropped by the host. For each link impacted by the system correlation, the C host system shall specify in argument Argument_Link_Track_Number_Choice, which LTN is to be retained and which LTN is to be dropped.
In the second case (new remote track correlation), the record NEW_REMOTE_TRACK_CORRELATION shall be used. The field SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER_RETAINED defines the system track number which will be used for the resulting track. For each link impacted by the system correlation, the C host system shall specify in argument Argument_Link_Track_Number_Choice, which LTN is to be retained and which LTN is to be dropped.
The field NUMBER_OF_BLOCKS shall be set with the number of arguments Argument_Link_Track_Number_Choice contained in the message.
The field SEQUENCE_NUMBER is used by the DLIP as a unique identification of the request and will be used to transmit an eventual response to the host.
The field RESPONSE_VALUE is only transmitted on datalinks that support the revert/reject protocol.

record.name: AHD335 CORRELATION RESPONSE
record.help:
This message is used by the host to respond to a remote correlation request previously received from a data-link. This message is used to accept, revert or reject the requested remote correlation. This message is the mandatory host response to a remote correlation request previously forwarded by the DLIP to the host (ADH334_DL_CORRELATION_REQUEST). This message may generate a message on the data links.
The host shall set the fields as follows: - The field HOST_CORRELATION_RESPONSE set according with the host decision, - The field CORRELATION_REQUEST_IDENTIFICATION set with the unique identification of the previously forwarded correlation request, - The field SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER_RETAINED set with the system track number to be retained by the DLIP as the resulting track.
For datalinks that support revert/reject protocol , in case of response from the host to a correlation revert response from the data link, an acceptation is mandatory.

record.name: AHD336 CHANGE LINK TRACK NUMBER
record.help: This message contains the allocation request of a new Link Track Number for a given system track. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon operator action to change the link track number of a given track. The LINK_TRACK_NUMBER field is the new one given by the operator. The DLIP will reject the request in the following cases : - The objet is engaged, - The objet is paired, - The objet is associated, - The objet is under control, - The objet is an IU, - The new TN is already in use, - The objet is a multisided line or area, - The object is received on the data link.

record.name: AHD337 FORCE LINK TRACK NUMBER
record.help: This message is used by the host to - force the association between a list of LTN (one LTN per Link Id) and a given system track or - to remove the association of a system track and a LTN for a list of link id. This message is used by a host to maintain the association between link track numbers (received on different links) and a system track number. The DLIP may or may not have yet received information on those remote tracks.

record.name: AHD360 MISSION ASSIGNMENT
record.help: This message contains necessary data to send a mission assignment message. This message shall be transmitted to the DLIP upon a controller operator request to assign a mission or an alert condition to a controlled unit. The record UNIT_IDENTIFIER_ADDRESSEE contains data to address this message to a given unit or to broadcast it on the data link. In case of COLLECTIVE_ADDRESS_INDICATOR field set, this message will be broadcasted with collective address value, the fields SYSTEM_TRACK_NUMBER and LINK_IDENTIFICATION will not be used by the DLIP.

record.name: AHD418 AWCIES TARGET
record.help:
This message contains all target data routed through AWCIES from a remote ACC site.
Data organization: The organization of a AHD418_AWCIES_TARGET is quite the same as a AHD118_TARGET message. The DLIP converts this message into a ADH118_TARGET message and reports it to its local host.
The Permanent_Bloc is described in the table below:

record.name: AHD419 AWCIES TARGET CORRELATION
record.help: This message contains the host system track number assignment to a routed target coming from a remote RPC site through AWCIES. It is processed as an AHD119 message.

record.name: TDH010 TRACK STAT REPORT
record.help: This message is a snapshot of the different DLIP surveillance counters concerning a given data link. Upon receipt of a THD010_TRACK_STAT_REQUEST message, the DLIP transmits this message to the host.

record.name: TDH032 HOUR TERM IND
record.help: This message gives the internal MIDS terminal time. This message is periodically transmitted by the DLIP to the host with a period of 1second.

record.name: TDH046 PU RECEPTION QUALITY
record.help:
This message contains the reception quality of a given L11 unit.
Data organization : TDH046_PU_RECEPTION_QUALITY = Permanent_Bloc + List_Of_Arguments
- Permanent_Bloc = Record HEADER + Permanent_Data. -- List_Of_Arguments = One OR more Reception_Quatily_from_PU. -- Reception_Quatily_from_PU = Element Reception_Quatily_from_PU. This message is transmitted by the DLIP upon reception of a reception quality message from the data link or upon transmission of own platform reception quality message on the data link.
The Permanent_Bloc is described in the table below :

record.name: TDH048 NET CYCLE TIME
record.help: This message reports the L11 net cycle time of a unit including own unit. This message is transmitted to the host upon receipt of a net cycle time message from the data link and also when the DLIP has computed his new net cycle time.

record.name: TDH049 MIDS RESPONSES
record.help:
This message carries blocks of FOM02 corresponding to the MIDS responses for all FIM01 sent by DLIP within the late FOM20 cycle. After the FOM20 is received the DLIP flushes all FOM02 received through this TDH049 message and and start storing new FOM02.
Message format: The TDH049_MIDS_RESPONSES has a variable size. It contains a permanent block and a variable part (Block1).

record.name: TDH053 L16ES STATUS
record.help: This message contains the status of all L16ES equipments connected to DLIP. This message is transmitted by the DLIP to the host periodically every 12 s and also when any data changes. Upon a TCP Discrete channel disconnection, DLIP removes the Resource (L16ES_ID) from the list in the TDH053_L16ES_STATUS and does not try by itself to reconnect to this equipment. It is the L16NCM responsibility to re-issue a new reconnection using (THD054_L16ES_CONNECTION_REQ). After a switch- over, DLIP does not re-establish the L16ES connections that were established before it.

record.name: TDH054 L16ES CONNECTION ANS
record.help: This message contains a report and a diagnostic in case the report is not OK. This answer is generated in response to a THD054_L16ES_CONNECTION_REQ.

record.name: TDH069 TDL STATUS
record.help: This message contains the status of a given data link and of the resources attached to it. This message is transmitted by the DLIP to the host periodically every 12 s and also when any data changes.

record.name: TDH070 OPEN RESOURCE ANS
record.help: This message contains a report and a diagnostic in case the report is not OK. This answer is generated in response to a THD070_OPEN_RESOURCE_REQ.

record.name: TDH071 CLOSE RESOURCE ANS
record.help: This message contains a report and a diagnostic in case the report is not OK. This message is generated in response to a THD071_CLOSE_RESOURCE_REQ.

record.name: TDH072 INIT LINK ANS
record.help: This message contains a report and a diagnostic in case the report is not OK. This message is generated in response to a THD072_INIT_LINK_REQ message.

record.name: TDH073 RESET LINK ANS
record.help: This message contains a report and a diagnostic in case the report is not OK. This message is generated in response to a THD073_RESET_LINK_REQ message.

record.name: TDH074 TDL CONTROL ANS
record.help: This message contains a report and a diagnostic in case the report is not OK. This message is generated in response to a THD074_TDL_CONTROL_REQ message.

record.name: TDH076 TERM INIT ANS
record.help: This message contains a report and a diagnostic in case the report is not OK. When the diagnostic is set to "Data Conflict" this message also contains the MIDS status word otherwise this field is not significant. This message is generated in response to a THD076_TERM_INIT_REQ message.

record.name: TDH077 LIST FILE TERM ANS
record.help: This message contains a report and a diagnostic in case the report is not OK. This message is generated in response to a THD077_LIST_FILE_TERM_REQ message.

record.name: TDH078 DEL FILE TERM ANS
record.help: This message contains a report and a diagnostic in case the report is not OK. This message is generated in response to a THD078_DEL_FILE_TERM_REQ message.

record.name: TDH079 ACT FILE TERM ANS
record.help: This message contains a report and a diagnostic in case the report is not OK. This message is generated in response to a THD079_ACT_FILE_TERM_REQ message.

record.name: TDH080 PARAM SEG TERM ANS
record.help: The purpose of this message is to convey the segment of the current parameters set of the MIDS terminal and the report of the corresponding request. In case the report is not OK, it also contains a diagnostic. This message is generated in response to a THD080_PARAM_SEG_TERM_REQ. The size of this message is variable. The field DATA_LENGTH_1 indicates the size of the segment conveyed in 16 bits word and also indicates the number of Block_1 that follow.

record.name: TDH081 PARAM TERM ANS
record.help: The purpose of this message is to convey an initialization file of the MIDS terminal and the report of the corresponding request. In case the report is not OK, it also contains a diagnostic. This message is generated in response to a THD081_PARAM_TERM_REQ message.

record.name: TDH082 NET MSG TRANSMIT ANS
record.help: This message reports the transmission status for a J message sent to the MIDS. For each message transmitted to the terminal, the DLIP will provide an acknowledgment message to the host.

record.name: TDH083 INIT TERM LOAD ANS
record.help: The purpose of this message is to report the status of an initialization data change. This message is generated by the DLIP in response to a THD083_INIT_TERM_LOAD_REQ message. The DIAG field shall only be interpreted if REPORT=NOK. If DIAG ="Data Conflict", this message also contains the MIDS status word otherwise this field is not significant.

record.name: TDH084 STATUS FILE ANS
record.help: The purpose of this message is to convey segments of a MIDS status file and the report of the corresponding request. In case the report is not OK, it also contains a diagnostic. This message is generated by the DLIP in response to a THD084_STATUS_FILE_REQ message. Data are valid only if REPORT=OK. On the contrary, the DIAG field shall only be interpreted if REPORT=NOK. The size of this message is variable. The field READ_LENGTH indicates how many bytes of the status file have been read and also indicates the number of Block_1 that follow.

record.name: TDH085 NET MSG EXCHANGED
record.help: This message reports a FIM or FOM messages received from the MIDS. The identifier of the FIM or FOM contained in this message is provided in the RECORDED_BLOCK_ID field. This message has a variable size. The field RECORDED_BLOCK_LG indicates the length in bytes of the block (FIM or FOM) recorded. The message contains only one FIM or one FOM recorded.

record.name: TDH086 TERM STATUS IND
record.help: The purpose of this message is to convey MIDS-LVT status information. This message is transmitted to the host periodically every 12 s and also when any data change.

record.name: TDH087 TERM PERM TEST ANS
record.help: This message reports the BIT of a MIDS. This message is generated in response to a THD087_TERM_PERM_TEST_REQ message.

record.name: TDH089 DEACT FILE TERM ANS
record.help: This message contains a report and a diagnostic in case the report is not OK. This message is generated in response to a THD089_DEACT_FILE_TERM_REQ message.

record.name: TDH090 INIT TERM LOAD IND
record.help: The purpose of this message is to notify any change in the MIDS-LVT initialization data file. This message is generated by the DLIP upon reception of any change in the MIDS initialization data file which is not generated by the THD076_TERM_INIT_REQ message. The message specifies the source of the init data change as well as the coordinates of the modified segment (offset in the file and length, the length including the offset) and the data that have changed. The size of this message is variable. The field DATA_LENGTH_1 indicates the size of the modified segment and also indicates the number of Block_1 that follow.

record.name: TDH091 TERM PERM TEST IND
record.help: This message reports the results of the terminal permanent BIT.

record.name: TDH092 NET MSG RECEIVED
record.help: This message reports to the host the TDL message received. Upon receipt of J messages, the DLIP will forward these messages to the host without changing their content or data link format.

record.name: TDH173 L16ES MESSAGE EXCHANGED
record.help: This message reports to L16NCM technical messages received from one L16ES. In a BOM, the length of the field L16ES_MESSAGE_LG (that is in byte) has to be converted in words of 16 bits. The DLIP sets the different fields in the message as follows : - L16ES_ID : identifier of the resource originating the technical message - L16ES_MESSAGE_OUT_ID : identifier of the technical message - L16ES_MESSAGE_LG : number of Block1 blocks that follow (size in byte of the technical message).

record.name: TDH311 TN RANGE STATUS
record.help: This message contains the data about the status of the track number range for a given link identification. This message is transmitted by the DLIP to the host upon : - host request (THD311_TN_RANGE_STATUS_REQUEST), - track number range pre-saturation (when 80%% of TNs are used), - end of pre-saturation (when rate of used TN returns below (80 minus TN_OFFSET_VALUE)%%), - track number range saturation (when 100%% of TNs are used), - end of saturation (when rate of used TN returns below (100 minus TN_OFFSET_VALUE)%%).

record.name: TDH400 APP INIT ANS
record.help:
This message is transmitted by the DLIP to acknowledge the THD400_APP_INIT_REQ message. TDH400_APP_INIT_ANS message is not itself subject to registration. It will be always addressed to the considered client application. The DLIP will acknowledge the THD400_APP_INIT_REQ message from an application by sending on the functional channel of the application this message. This message will report the status of the initialization. In the message TDH400_APP_INIT_ANS if the CONNECTION_REPORT field is set to REFUSED, the CONNECTION_DIAG field will contain the rejection reason given by the DLIP. See also channel_4 connection protocole.
Message format: The TDH400_APP_INIT_ANS has a constant size. It only contains a permanent bloc.

record.name: TDH441 CONNECTION ANS
record.help:
This message has two purposes : - to acknowledge the client application THD441_CONNECTION_REQ message, - to pass to client application the DLIP internet address and the DLIP TCP port that the client will use to establish the functional connection (if an INITIALISATION has been requested). See connection protocole flow chart.
Message format: The TDH441_CONNECTION_ANS has a variable size. It can have one of the two following formats depending on the value of DATA_BLOCK_IDENTIFICATION of Block1.

record.name: TDH442 DLIP STATUS
record.help:
This message is transmitted each 12 seconds by the DLIP once it is started and instantaneously when a new client application has just been connected or disconnected to/from a functional connection. See connection protocole flow chart.
Message format: The TDH442_DLIP_STATUS has a variable size. It contains a permanent block and a variable part (Block1).

record.name: TDH500 MX512PV SET CONFIG ANS
record.help: This message contains the response to the THD500_MX512PV_SET_CONFIG_REQ message.

record.name: TDH501 MX512PV SET LIST OF PU ANS
record.help: This message contains the response to the THD501_MX512PV_SET_LIST_OF_PU_REQ message.

record.name: TDH502 MX512PV GET CONFIG ANS
record.help: This message contains the response to the THD502_MX512PV_GET_CONFIG_REQ message. If the REPORT is not OK, there is no other block than the permanent block reported in this message. If the REPORT is OK, the DLIP always reports the Block_1 followed by the Block_2. The other blocks are provisions for future evolutions.

record.name: TDH503 MX512PV GET LIST OF PU ANS
record.help: This message contains the response to the THD503_MX512PV_GET_LIST_OF_PU_REQ message.

record.name: TDH504 MX512PV BIT ANS
record.help: This message contains the response to the THD504_MX512PV_BIT_REQ message. It contains the BIT status of the MX512PV DTS. If REPORT is not OK only permanent bloc is reported in this message. If REPORT is OK: Block_2 is always reported for any site and Block_3 is only reported if MXDTS_SITE_RADIO_TYPE is SPLIT_RADIO_SITE or SPLIT_SPLIT_SITE.

record.name: TDH505 MX512PV RESET ANS
record.help: This message contains the response to the THD505_MX512PV_RESET_REQ message.

record.name: TDH506 MX512PV STATUS
record.help: This message contains the permanent status of the MX512PV DTS reported by the DLIP every 12 seconds or upon change.

record.name: THD010 TRACK STAT REQUEST
record.help: This message is used by the host to request track statistics for a given data link. This message is transmitted by the host upon host data link statistics request.

record.name: THD013 L11 BIASES
record.help: This message contains the delta_X, delta_Y and delta_Angle biases to be applied for the translational and rotational correction for a given L11A link.

record.name: THD044 DLRP
record.help:
This message reports the latitude and longitude of the data link reference point (DLRP) or the corrected DLRP for the specified link identification. The host sends this message to DLIP - during the initialization phase of a L11 or L14 data link, - after a DLRP update, - after the host has computed a corrected DLRP. In this last case, the field CORRECTED_DLRP_INDICATOR shall be set to INDICATOR_ON or - upon DLRP transmission or stop tranmission request from the host.
If DLRP_APPLICATION_INDICATOR is set to INDICATOR_ON, the DLIP store this DLRP (or corrected DLRP) and use it for future coordinate conversions. In case of CORRECTED_DLRP_INDICATOR field set to NO_STATEMENTand if DLRP_TRANSMISSION_INDICATOR is set to INDICATOR_ON, the DLIP send this new DLRP in a M9G message on the data link. In case of transmission required, the DLIP use the DLRP_TRANSMIT_RULE_MODE field value to send the M9G periodically, for a predetermined time or to stop the current transmission.

record.name: THD045 SCC
record.help:
This message defines the system co-ordinate centre (SCC) position used for L11 data position coding. The host transmit this message when it wants the DLIP to use an SCC for data position coding on L11 in place of own platform position (USING_SCC_INDICATOR = USE_SCC) or when he wants to return to the use of own platform position (USING_SCC_INDICATOR = USE_OWN_POSITION).
The DLIP will reject this co-ordinate centre in case of impossibility to encode it into the M1 message and will alert the host when : a) If Dlat %%lt; -1023.984375 minutes or Dlat %%gt; 1023.984375 minutes b) If DLRP lat %%lt; 60 degrees and (Dlong %%lt; -1023.984375 minutes or Dlong %%gt; 1023.984375 minutes c) If DLRP long %%gt; or = 60 degrees and (Dlong %%lt; -2047.96875 minutes or Dlong %%gt; 2047.96875 minutes with Dlat = delta latitude between SCC lat and DLRP lat with Dlong = delta longitude between SCC long and DLRP long

record.name: THD047 GRU UNIT DESIGNATION
record.help: This message is used to provide the PU track number of the Grid Reference Unit. This message is transmitted by the host to the DLIP to provide the track number of the GRU Participating Unit. The GRU_TRACK_NUMBER field shall contain the track number of a known unit operating on the data link identified by the LINK_IDENTIFICATION field. If GRU_TRACK_NUMBER field contains the track number of a remote unit, all tracks received from this unit by the DLIP are transmitted to the host regardless of filtering and R rules. If GRU_TRACK_NUMBER field contains the own unit track number, the host shall use the AHD159_SET_DLTRACK_TRANSMISSION_MODE message to force the transmission of each selected track on the data link.

record.name: THD054 L16ES CONNECTION REQ
record.help: This request asks for a TCP Discrete channel connection or a disconnection to a L16ES equipment depending on the value of L16ES_CON_ACTION field. The DLIP will generate a TDH054_L16ES_CONNECTION_ANS in response to this request. If L16ES_CON_ACTION value is "DISCONNECT_FROM_L16ES" the "L16ES_IP_ADDRESS" field is not used by DLIP.

field.name: BY ADDRESS OR BY HOSTNAME DIS

record.name: THD070 OPEN RESOURCE REQ
record.help: This request ask for a resource connection and attaches it to a LINK_ID. The DLIP will generate a TDH070_OPEN_RESOURCE_ANS in response to this request.

field.name: BY ADDRESS OR BY HOSTNAME DIS
BY ADDRESS OR BY HOSTNAME DIS

record.name: THD071 CLOSE RESOURCE REQ
record.help: This request is used to stop the participation of a resource on a given link. DLIP automatically de-activate this resource (same as THD074_TDL_CONTROL_REQ) and closes the TCP connection with it. In response to this request the DLIP will generate a TDH071_CLOSE_RESOURCE_ANS.

record.name: THD072 INIT LINK REQ
record.help: This message is used to open and initialize a DLIP data link. A THD072_INIT_LINK_REQ message will be transmitted by the host only during the initialization phase of a considered data link . In other case it will be rejected.

record.name: THD073 RESET LINK REQ
record.help:
Resets a given link. There are three kinds of reset : Initialization data reset, Tactical data reset or Initialization and tactical data reset. An Init And Tactical Data reset may be performed only when the link state is "Initialized" and has the following consequences : - the initialization data ( own link TN and link TN range) are cleared. - the remote data objects are cleared. - in addition, if not already closed by a "close ressource" , the DLIP close all the connected ressources (TCP connection closed, IP address cleared and asset filters cleared) - the link state goes to "Off".
A Tactical Data reset may be performed when the link state is "Initialized" or "Off" and has the following consequences : - the remote data objects are cleared. - the link state does not change.
An Initialization Data reset may be performed only when the link state is "Initialized" and has the following consequences : - the initialization data ( own link TN and Link TN range) are cleared. - in addition, if not already closed by a "close ressource" , the DLIP close all the connected ressources (TCP connection closed, IP address cleared and asset filters cleared) - the link state goes to "Off". In response to this request the DLIP will generate a TDH073_RESET_LINK_ANS.

record.name: THD074 TDL CONTROL REQ
record.help: This message is used to control a resource (Activation, De-activation). In response to a THD074_TDL_CONTROL_REQ message the DLIP will transmit a TDH074_TDL_CONTROL_ANS to the considered application. When the field DATA_LINK_RESOURCE_ACTIVATION is set to DEACTIVATE_ALL the field RESOURCE_ID is ignored as all the resources are concerned. In this case the field RESOURCE_ID should be set to 0.

record.name: THD076 TERM INIT REQ
record.help: This message is a request for loading an entire initialization file in the MIDS terminal. In response to this request the DLIP will generate a TDH076_TERM_INIT_ANS. The request is rejected if there is already one other THD076_TERM_INIT_REQ or a THD083_INIT_TERM_LOAD_REQ in progress in the DLIP.

record.name: THD077 LIST FILE TERM REQ
record.help: This message is a request addressed to the DLIP to report the list of initialization files stored in the MIDS. In response to this message the DLIP will generate a TDH077_LIST_FILE_TERM_ANS,

record.name: THD078 DEL FILE TERM REQ
record.help: This message is a request addressed to the DLIP to remove an initialization file stored in the MIDS. In response to this message the DLIP will generate a TDH078_DEL_FILE_TERM_ANS message.

record.name: THD079 ACT FILE TERM REQ
record.help: This message is a request to the DLIP to activate an initialization stored file in the MIDS. In response to this message the DLIP will generate a TDH079_ACT_FILE_TERM_ANS message.

record.name: THD080 PARAM SEG TERM REQ
record.help: The purpose of this message is to request a segment (contiguous 16-bit words) of the current initialization data file of the MIDS-LV terminal. This message specifies the first word to read and the total number of bytes, which has to be an even number.

record.name: THD081 PARAM TERM REQ
record.help: The purpose of this message is to request an initialization file of the MIDS terminal. This message specifies the index number of the file to read.

record.name: THD082 NET MSG TRANSMIT REQ
record.help:
This message is a request addressed to the DLIP to transmit a J message on the data link. The message will contain all the data necessary for the MIDS for transmission. The size of this message is variable. The field MSG_LG indicates the number of 80 bits word the J message is made of and also indicates the number of Block_1 that follow.
The correspondances between the THD082 message and the FIM01 message are : MSG_CODING = PACKING LIMIT MSG_PRIO = PRIORITY Field MESSAGE ID of FIM01 is auto-incremented by DLIP between 0 to 999 when DEM_LOOPBACK is True HOST_ACK_REC_INDIC = R/C MSG_ACK_ID = R/C MESSAGE ID MSG_AGE_(MIN,SEC,MILLISEC,MICROSEC) = TIME TAG MSG_STALENESS = STALENESS LIMIT REPROM_RR = REPROMULGATION RECURRENCE RATE REPROM_COUNTER = REPROM COUNTER REPROM = REPROM REQUEST EXTRAPOLATION = EXTRAPOL REQUEST INDIC_J12_6 = TSMI STN = SOURCE TRACK NUMBER LOCAL_DEST_IND = ADDI TRANS_METHOD = TRANSMIT METHOD SLOT = SLOT NUMBER SET = SET PG = PG NEEDLINE = NEEDLINE ID
The word I/J of the FIM01 is always forced to 1 (Transmit Link 16 Only). The word TYPE of the FIM01 is always forced to 0 (Link 16 Fixed Format)

record.name: THD083 INIT TERM LOAD REQ
record.help: The purpose of this message is to modify a segment (contiguous 16-bit words) of the current initialization data file of the MIDS-LV terminal. The message provides the data to be loaded and the offset of the segment (this offset is the first word of the segment to be modified). The size of this message is variable. The field DATA_LENGTH_1 indicates the number of 16 bits words of the segment and also indicates the number of Block_1 that follow. The request is rejected if there is already one THD076_INIT_TERM_REQ or an other THD083_INIT_TERM_LOAD_REQ in progress in the DLIP.

record.name: THD084 STATUS FILE REQ
record.help: Asks a segment of the MIDS status file. In response to this request the DLIP will send a TDH084_STATUS_FILE_ANS containing the requested data.

record.name: THD087 TERM PERM TEST REQ
record.help: This message is a request addressed to a MIDS to start the MIDS test. Caution : this request may affect MIDS operational running. It is preferable to de-activate the MIDS before sending this request. In response to this message the DLIP generates a TDH087_TERM_PERM_TEST_ANS message.

record.name: THD089 DEACT FILE TERM REQ
record.help: This request de-activates the current file in the MIDS. In response to this message the DLIP will generate a TDH089_DEACT_FILE_TERM_ANS message.

record.name: THD170 TACTICAL FILTER
record.help:
This message contains all information about a filter description.
Data organisation :
THD170_TACTICAL_FILTER = Permanent_Bloc + List_Of_Arguments.
- Permanent_Block = Record HEADER + Permanent_Data. - List_Of_Arguments = 0 OR more Arguments. -- Argument = Argument_Filter_Type. --- Argument_Filter_Type = Header_Of_Block + Record Filter type description. This message is transmitted by the host system to the DLIP when the host decide to implement a filter either in transmission, reception or both. The reception of reception filter concerning a data link supersedes the previous reception filter on this data link. Same for transmission. The reception of a filter to be implemented in transmission and reception concerning a data link supersedes the previous both reception and transmission filter on this data link. If the host system wants to remove a filter from a data link, it only needs to send this message with the permanent block.
The Permanent_Block is described in the table below :

record.name: THD172 ASSET FILTER
record.help:
This message contains all information about a filter description for a given L16 resource.
Data organisation :
THD172_ASSET_FILTER = Permanent_Bloc + List_Of_Arguments.
- Permanent_Bloc = Record HEADER + Permanent_Data. - List_Of_Arguments = 0 OR more Arguments. -- Argument = Argument_Filter_Type. --- Argument_Filter_Type = Header_Of_Arg + Record Filter type description. This message is transmitted by the L16NCM host system to the DLIP when the host decides to implement a filter in transmission. (asset filtering in reception is not implemented). The receipt of a transmission filter (a complete THD172 message) concerning a resource supersedes the previous transmission filter on this resource. The asset filters associated to a resource by the DLIP on THD172 reception are cleared when a THD071_CLOSE_RESOURCE_REQ or a THD072_RESET_LINK_REQ is received. If the L16NCM host system wants to remove a filter from a resource, it only needs to send this message with the permanent block.
A THD172 message defines a filter composed of elementary filters. An elementary filter is described by a bloc. The number of elementary filters is given by the field NUMBER_OF_FILTERS and indicates the number of blocs that follow.
The Permanent_Bloc is described in the table below :

record.name: THD173 L16ES MESSAGE EXCHANGED
record.help: This message is used by L16NCM to transmit technical messages to one L16ES. In a BIM, the length of the field L16ES_MESSAGE_LG (that is in byte) has to be convert in words of 16 bits. The equipment specified in the field L16ES_ID must be in CONNECTED state.

record.name: THD311 TN RANGE STATUS REQUEST
record.help: This message is used by the host to request status about track number range of a given link identification. This message is transmitted by the host upon host track number range status request.

record.name: THD400 APP INIT REQ
record.help:
This message is used to initialize the exchanges between the DLIP and an application. The THD400_APP_INIT_REQ message defines the list of DLIP messages expected by the application. Only these messages will be routed from the DLIP to the client application. No message will be processed by the DLIP on both directions of the functional channel before the THD400_APP_INIT_REQ has been received and correctly acknowledged by DLIP (through the TDH400_APP_INIT_ANS message). Once this message has been received and acknowledged the first time, functional exchanges can start. Nevertheless, an application can send a new THD400_APP_INIT_REQ at any moment. In such a case the new registration will replace the older one (no merge is done). Messages of the old registration that are in transit to the client application (in the TCP/IP layers) will be delivered any way. See also channel_4 flow chart.
Message format: The THD400_APP_INIT_REQ has a variable size. It contains a permanent block and a variable part (Block1).

record.name: THD413 ROUTING FILTER
record.help:
This message contains a routing filter. A routing filter is applied on target report messages (J12.6) which have to be routed to a remote RPC site for correlation with a system track. There is one routing filter per remote RPC site adjacent to the ACC. A routing filter is a polygon filter.
A target report (J12.6) will be routed to the first remote RPC site for which the target is located inside its corresponding routing filter. Routing filters are applied starting from the first filter set to the last filter set by the DLCM. This message will be sent by the DLCM link controller just after the Link 16 initialisation. A Routing filter override the previous one for a given remote RPC site. To reset a routing filter the DLCM link controller must send an update of this routing filter with the field NUMBER_OF_POLYGON_POINTS=0.
This message is composed of a permanent block (described just below) followed by as many Block_1 as points there are in the polygon filter.

record.name: THD441 CONNECTION REQ
record.help:
A client application will send this message to request a functional connection with the DLIP. This message is composed of: - the unique client application identifier - the client internet address and the client TCP/UDP port that the DLIP will use to establish the functional connection
This message is also sent by a client application to close a functional connection. See connection protocole flow chart.
As in UDP, datagrams can be lost, it is the client application responsibility to re-transmit a connection request if no answer is received after a time-out of 2 seconds.
Message format: The THD441_CONNECTION_REQ has a variable size. It can have one of the two following formats depending on the value of DATA_BLOCK_IDENTIFICATION of Block1.

record.name: THD442 DLIP STATUS REQUEST
record.help:
Upon receipt of this message the active DLIP will send its TDH442_DLIP_STATUS. This enable new client applications to get more rapidly the DLIP informations (NAME, ID, STATE) contained in the DLIP_STATUS without having to wait a new recurrence of this message (which is otherwise transmitted each 12 seconds by the DLIP). As in UDP, datagrams can be lost, it is the client application responsibility to re-transmit this request if no answer is received after a time-out of 2 seconds.
Message format: The THD442_DLIP_STATUS_REQUEST has a fixed size. Field RESERVED is not used and its value is not examined by the DLIP.

record.name: THD500 MX512PV SET CONFIG REQ
record.help:
This message is used to transmit a configuration request to the MX-512PV DTS. In response to a THD500_MX512PV_SET_CONFIG_REQ message the DLIP will transmit a TDH_MX512PV_SET_CONFIG_ANS to the considered application. The DLIP always expects a THD500 with a Block_1 followed by a Block_2. The other blocks are provisions for future evolutions.
The MXDTS_START_RESET_COMMAND is automatically set to OFFLINE by the DTS if the at one of the other parameters are changed. A host cannot therefore change the configuration and start the PICKET interrogation (or start BROADCAST/SHORT BROADCAST transmission) in the same THD500. So, the host shall send a first THD500 to set the configuration. Then a second THD500 with MXDTS_START_RESET_COMMAND=ONLINE and the other fields at the same value as the first THD500 to really start PICKET interrogation (or start BROADCAST/SHORT BROADCAST transmission). We highly recommend to set MXDTS_START_RESET_COMMAND=OFFLINE in the first THD500. The status of the MXDTS_START_RESET_COMMAND corresponds to the field DTS mode as NCS in the Control Request Message of the DTS ICD (which is a little bit confusing). Its current state returned by the DTS is provided in the TDH500 and the TDH502.

record.name: THD503 MX512PV GET LIST OF PU REQ
record.help: This message asks for the current list of PUs loaded in the MX512PV DTS. This request is always addressed to the local DTS.

record.name: THD504 MX512PV BIT REQ
record.help: This message asks for the BIT STATUS of the MX512PV DTS. This command is only allowed when the L11A is de-activated. The MXDTS_SITE_RADIO_TYPE field is necessary to know how many DTS are involved in the configuration and to address that request to all of them (even if DLIP only report to host the global result through the TDH504).

record.name: THD505 MX512PV RESET REQ
record.help: This message asks for the execution of the RESET of the MX512PV DTS. This command is not destructive but it leads to TCP disconnection with the DTS. Therefore it will only be accepted when the L11A is de-activated. The MXDTS_SITE_RADIO_TYPE field is necessary to know how many DTS are involved in the configuration and to address that request to all of them (even if DLIP only report to host the global result through the TDH505).

element.help: This field gives the target bearing referenced to true north.

element.name: DELTA ELEVATION
element.help: This field gives the difference in vertical distance from a beacon to a target. In one foot increments. Values 0 through 16383 means 0 through 16383 feet values 16385 through 32767 means -16383 through -1 feet.

element.name: BEACON CODE
element.help: CODING TO BE DETERMINED.

element.name: LASER ILLUMINATOR CODE
element.help: A four digit code used by laser designators and laser weapons. The sixteen bits are divided into four groups of four bits. Each group is interpreted independently. For each group, values 10 to 15 are illegal.

element.name: APP LOGICAL ID
element.help: This field indicates the identification of a remote client application.

element.name: PROTOCOL
element.help: This field indicates which protocol will be used in a functional connection. The DLIP always acts as a TCP server.

element.name: INTERNET ADDRESS
element.help: This Field indicates an internet address XX.YY.ZZ.WW This is a table of four 8 bits unsigned integer (1st is XX, 2nd is YY, 3rd is ZZ and 4th is WW)

element.name: PORT
element.help: This field indicates a TCP or UDP port number.

element.name: MXDTS WAVEFORM
element.help: This field indicates the waveform used for radio transmission/reception by the DTS.

element.name: MXDTS RECEIVE SIDE BAND
element.help: This field indicates the DTS receive mode.

element.name: MXDTS TIMING RATE
element.help: This field gives the frame rate used by the DTS.

element.name: MXDTS STATUS
element.help: This field gives the global status.

element.name: BY ADDRESS OR BY HOSTNAME DIS
element.help: This field indicates if the connection parameter given in the same message is an IP address or a hostname.

element.name: LTN BLOCK
element.help: TRACK_NUMBER_REFERENCE and TRACK_NUMBER_ADDRESSEE are merged

element.name: INDICATOR 1
element.help: Depending of the name of the field 0: NO_STATEMENT, INACTIVE or OFF.

element.name: NUMBER OF POLYGON POINTS
element.help: This field gives the number of points that compose a polygon filter area.

element.name: IN OUT INDICATOR
element.help: This field indicates if the filter blocked the object inside (IN) or outside (OUT) the area.

element.name: BYPASS BLOCK INDICATOR
element.help: This field indicates if the filter is a Bypass filter or a Block filter. If the filter is "Bypass" type , data selected by the filter is retained. If the filter is "Block" type, data selected by the filter is discarded.

element.name: RADIUS
element.help: Contains the radius of a circle.
